      "type": "heading",
      "value": "What is a Type Alias?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "A type alias allows you to create a custom name for a type, making complex types easier to reuse and manage."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Basic Example"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "typescript",
      "value": "type Name = string;\nlet userName: Name = 'John';"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Object Type Alias"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "typescript",
      "value": "type User = {\n  name: string;\n  age: number;\n};"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Union Type Alias"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "typescript",
      "value": "type ID = string | number;"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Function Type Alias"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "typescript",
      "value": "type AddFn = (a: number, b: number) => number;"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Intersection Types"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "typescript",
      "value": "type A = { name: string };\ntype B = { age: number };\n\ntype Person = A & B;"
    },
